{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"7c17eaa0-57de-5e7a-b500-9ccd788b06fd","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6cde9389-f0c9-4b68-bed5-b61c23e4984b --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 6cde9389-f0c9-4b68-bed5-b61c23e4984b -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 1be6e6a2-2e67-4b5f-84a9-929b5930b9f2 --><!-- begin field 79e77bc7-1937-4435-849b-354af166bbac --><ul><li>In England, overall 31% of men and 16% of women drink alcohol at levels above the <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/background-information/definition/\">low risk drinking guidelines</a>, with the highest proportion in the 15 to 64 age group.</li><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/background-information/definition/\">Alcohol dependence</a> affects 4% of people aged between 16 and 65 in England (6% of men and 2% of women).</li><li>Alcohol-use disorder (based on <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/background-information/definition/\">DSM-V criteria</a>) is a common psychiatric disorder with lifetime prevalence estimates of 7% to 12.5% in most Western countries. <ul><li>Men outnumber women by a ratio of more than 2 to 1, although the disorder is probably under-reported in females.</li><li>Alcohol-use disorder is uncommon in countries with large Muslim populations, and is most common in European countries.</li><li>In primary care settings, the prevalence of alcohol-use disorders ranges from 20% to 36%.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/references/\">NICE, 2010b</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/references/\">Connor et al, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2017a</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/alcohol-problem-drinking/references/\">PHE, 2017</a>] </p><!-- end field 79e77bc7-1937-4435-849b-354af166bbac --><!-- end item 1be6e6a2-2e67-4b5f-84a9-929b5930b9f2 -->","topic":{"id":"b9a3dde8-c412-5195-8fde-5edce1ca90ef","topicId":"a79c6a40-2a77-4966-b622-3f9098a20bcc","topicName":"Alcohol - problem drinking","slug":"alcohol-problem-drinking","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2018","chapters":[{"id":"2aa1ce9d-21b4-5104-a4bf-15a4b8afccc5","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"3a955db5-e8e3-5bc7-b5c8-f5940784faf3","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"03d8357e-0ebd-5b7d-8568-d7e8d49950e8","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"075aaa53-3fe1-53c4-9cc9-29f69e0bffec","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"21a8264a-bc66-5d6d-8227-a880d7ba88fa","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"301870c8-5648-58c4-83b9-e79fd21180b1","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9b90341c-287d-52ac-bcc0-8d8b16e4f542","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"e3c4a028-9ac0-565c-972e-274f11fe5c7d","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0e0836b8-6902-52e4-9a8c-a99ee9b6f14a","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"3c97251b-f617-559e-9cbf-6a85e3fa0274","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"a8b5d23b-a866-5e99-8e10-6fa0661a7ea6","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"790177cb-1bcf-5462-8853-b5d7ac246735","slug":"nice-quality-sta